Chat opened from the plan tab was a local DOM overlay inside `plan.html`'s iframe, disconnected from the shell-level overlay used by all other tabs — causing inconsistent sizing and losing chat state on tab switch. Separately, the analytics tab header exposed a collapse toggle that should not be user-controllable.

## Chat — one shared shell overlay for all tabs (`plan.html`)

`openChat()` now delegates to the shell when running as a regular embedded tab:

```js
function openChat() {
    // In regular embedded tab (not shellChat overlay) delegate to the shell's shared chat
    if (document.documentElement.getAttribute('data-embedded-tab') === '1' &&
        document.documentElement.getAttribute('data-shell-chat') !== '1') {
        requestShellAction('NUTRIPLAN_OPEN_CHAT');
        return;
    }
    // existing logic runs only inside the shellChat iframe itself
    ...
}
```

- All tabs now open the same `spaShellChatFrame` overlay (`plan.html?chat=1&embedded=1&shellChat=1`)
- Chat content persists across tab switches — the iframe is hidden/shown, not destroyed
- `shellChat` guard prevents infinite delegation when the overlay iframe calls `openChat()` on load

## Analytics container — permanently expanded (`game-analytics.html`)

- Removed `onclick`/`role="button"`/`tabindex`/keyboard handler from `.game-analytics-header`
- Removed chevron icon and its CSS (`.game-analytics-chevron`, `cursor:pointer`, `user-select`)
- Removed `toggleGameAnalytics()` function entirely
- Container initialises expanded and has no collapse affordance
